         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we study the rotational form of the pressure-correction method that was proposed by Timmermans, Minev, and Van De Vosse. We show that the rotational form of the algorithm provides better accuracy in terms of the H<sup>1</sup>-norm of the velocity and of the L<sup>2</sup>-norm of the pressure than the standard form.</p>
          </abstract>
